verses.text: And it came to pass in the twelfth year , in the twelfth month , in the first \add day\add* of the month , \add that\add* the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came unto me, saying ,

Son of man , take up a lamentation for Pharaoh king of Egypt , and say unto him, Thou art like a young lion of the nations , and thou \add art\add* as a whale in the seas : and thou camest forth with thy rivers , and troubledst the waters with thy feet , and fouledst their rivers.\f + \fr 32.2 \ft whale: or, dragon\f*
Thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; I will therefore spread out my net over thee with a company of many people ; and they shall bring thee up in my net.

Then will I leave thee upon the land , I will cast thee forth upon the open field , and will cause all the fowls of the heaven to remain upon thee, and I will fill the beasts of the whole earth with thee.
And I will lay thy flesh upon the mountains , and fill the valleys with thy height.

I will also water with thy blood the land wherein thou swimmest , \add even\add* to the mountains ; and the rivers shall be full of thee.\f + \fr 32.6 \ft the land wherein…: or, the land of thy swimming\f*

And when I shall put thee out , I will cover the heaven , and make the stars thereof dark ; I will cover the sun with a cloud , and the moon shall not give her light.\f + \fr 32.7 \ft put…: or, extinguish thee\f*

All the bright lights of heaven will I make dark over thee, and set darkness upon thy land , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 32.8 \ft bright…: Heb. lights of the light in heaven\f*\f + \fr 32.8 \ft dark: Heb. them dark\f*

I will also vex the hearts of many people , when I shall bring thy destruction among the nations , into the countries which thou hast not known.\f + \fr 32.9 \ft vex: Heb. provoke to anger, or, grief\f*

Yea, I will make many people amazed at thee, and their kings shall be horribly afraid for thee, when I shall brandish my sword before them ; and they shall tremble at \add every\add* moment , every man for his own life , in the day of thy fall. \p
¶ For thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; The sword of the king of Babylon shall come upon thee.
By the swords of the mighty will I cause thy multitude to fall , the terrible of the nations , all of them: and they shall spoil the pomp of Egypt , and all the multitude thereof shall be destroyed.
I will destroy also all the beasts thereof from beside the great waters ; neither shall the foot of man trouble them any more, nor the hoofs of beasts trouble them.
Then will I make their waters deep , and cause their rivers to run like oil , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.

When I shall make the land of Egypt desolate , and the country shall be destitute of that whereof it was full , when I shall smite all them that dwell therein, then shall they know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 32.15 \ft destitute…: Heb. desolate from the fulness thereof\f*

This \add is\add* the lamentation wherewith they shall lament her: the daughters of the nations shall lament her: they shall lament for her, \add even\add* for Egypt , and for all her multitude , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*. \p
¶ It came to pass also in the twelfth year , in the fifteenth \add day\add* of the month , \add that\add* the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came unto me, saying ,

Son of man , wail for the multitude of Egypt , and cast them down , \add even\add* her, and the daughters of the famous nations , unto the nether parts of the earth , with them that go down into the pit.
Whom dost thou pass in beauty ? go down , and be thou laid with the uncircumcised.
They shall fall in the midst of \add them that are\add* slain by the sword : she is delivered to the sword : draw her and all her multitudes.\f + \fr 32.20 \ft she…: or, the sword is laid\f*
The strong among the mighty shall speak to him out of the midst of hell with them that help him: they are gone down , they lie uncircumcised , slain by the sword.
Asshur \add is\add* there and all her company : his graves \add are\add* about him: all of them slain , fallen by the sword :

Whose graves are set in the sides of the pit , and her company is round about her grave : all of them slain , fallen by the sword , which caused terror in the land of the living.\f + \fr 32.23 \ft terror: or, dismaying\f*

There \add is\add* Elam and all her multitude round about her grave , all of them slain , fallen by the sword , which are gone down uncircumcised into the nether parts of the earth , which caused their terror in the land of the living ; yet have they borne their shame with them that go down to the pit.

They have set her a bed in the midst of the slain with all her multitude : her graves \add are\add* round about him: all of them uncircumcised , slain by the sword : though their terror was caused in the land of the living , yet have they borne their shame with them that go down to the pit : he is put in the midst of \add them that be\add* slain.

There \add is\add* Meshech , Tubal , and all her multitude : her graves \add are\add* round about him: all of them uncircumcised , slain by the sword , though they caused their terror in the land of the living.

And they shall not lie with the mighty \add that are\add* fallen of the uncircumcised , which are gone down to hell with their weapons of war : and they have laid their swords under their heads , but their iniquities shall be upon their bones , though \add they were\add* the terror of the mighty in the land of the living.\f + \fr 32.27 \ft with their…: Heb. with weapons of their war\f*
Yea, thou shalt be broken in the midst of the uncircumcised , and shalt lie with \add them that are\add* slain with the sword.

There \add is\add* Edom , her kings , and all her princes , which with their might are laid by \add them that were\add* slain by the sword : they shall lie with the uncircumcised , and with them that go down to the pit.\f + \fr 32.29 \ft laid: Heb. given, or, put\f*

There \add be\add* the princes of the north , all of them, and all the Zidonians , which are gone down with the slain ; with their terror they are ashamed of their might ; and they lie uncircumcised with \add them that be\add* slain by the sword , and bear their shame with them that go down to the pit.
Pharaoh shall see them, and shall be comforted over all his multitude , \add even\add* Pharaoh and all his army slain by the sword , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.

For I have caused my terror in the land of the living : and he shall be laid in the midst of the uncircumcised with \add them that are\add* slain with the sword , \add even\add* Pharaoh and all his multitude , saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.
